cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.CYBER, cs.GR 

The paper describes the design and implementation of a tool for visually cataloguing and retrieving data associated with a given geographical location through a web-based Google Maps interface. The tool involves the integration of web-based mapping services with scientific data repositories, which suggests that it could fall under several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the management and curation of scientific data repositories. 

cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper discusses the challenges of querying and retrieving data from multiple sources via a common interface. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper deals with the retrieval of scientific data based on geographical location. 

cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) is a less likely category, but the paper does mention some security concerns related to the sharing of scientific data. 

cs.GR (Graphics) is also a less likely category, but the paper does involve the use of a web-based Google Maps interface for visualizing data.
